---
import StudyLayout from '../layouts/StudyLayout.astro';

// Verified 2026-06-10 against the Claude Certified Architect - Foundations
// exam guide: https://claudecertifications.com/claude-certified-architect/exam-guide
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

// Domain weights mirror the sidebar (src/content/navigation/structure.json).
const domains = [
  { id: '1', title: 'Agentic Architecture & Orchestration', weight: '27%' },
  { id: '2', title: 'Tool Design & MCP Integration', weight: '18%' },
  { id: '3', title: 'Claude Code Configuration & Workflows', weight: '20%' },
  { id: '4', title: 'Prompt Engineering & Structured Output', weight: '20%' },
  { id: '5', title: 'Context Management & Reliability', weight: '15%' },
];
---

<StudyLayout title="About the Exam">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="kicker">// META</div>
    <h1>About the Exam</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The <b>Claude Certified Architect &ndash; Foundations</b> exam is Anthropic's first official
      technical certification. It is built for solution architects designing production applications
      with Claude, and it is scenario-based rather than a memorization test.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Format</h2>
      <div class="facts">
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Issued by</span><span class="fv">Anthropic</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Style</span><span class="fv">Scenario-based, multiple choice</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Scenarios</span><span class="fv">4 of 6, drawn at random</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Audience</span><span class="fv">Solution architects building on Claude</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Cost</span><span class="fv">Free for the first 5,000 partner-company employees</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Access</span><span class="fv">Request via Anthropic's Skilljar portal</span></div>
      </div>
      <p>
        Each of the four scenarios you draw places you in a real production context and asks you to make
        architectural decisions. See <a class="xlink" href={`${base}/exam-scenarios`}>The 6 Scenarios</a> for
        the full list and the skills each one tests.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Domains &amp; Weighting</h2>
      <p>Five domains, weighted by how much of the exam draws on each. The sidebar mirrors these.</p>
      <ul class="domains">
        {domains.map((d) => (
          <li>
            <span class="dname"><span class="dnum">D{d.id}</span>{d.title}</span>
            <span class="dweight">{d.weight}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Scoring</h2>
      <div class="facts">
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Passing score</span><span class="fv">720 / 1000</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="fk">Scenarios drawn</span><span class="fv">4 of 6, at random</span></div>
      </div>
      <p>
        Because you cannot predict which four scenarios appear, prepare for all six. A weak spot in any one
        scenario is a gap you cannot route around on test day.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</StudyLayout>

<style>
  .wrap { padding-top: 60px; max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .kicker {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.6);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    color: var(--neon-lime);
    text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(157, 255, 60, 0.6), 3px 3px 0 rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.3);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .lead {
    margin: 18px 0 36px;
    max-width: 760px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .lead b { color: var(--neon-lime); text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(157, 255, 60, 0.5); }
  section { margin-bottom: 40px; }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.4);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  p { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 12px; max-width: 760px; }

  .facts {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .fact {
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background: var(--panel);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .fact .fk {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--neon-amber);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .fact .fv { font-size: 0.86rem; color: var(--text); }

  .domains { list-style: none; margin-top: 8px; }
  .domains li {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background: var(--panel);
    padding: 12px 16px;
    margin: 8px 0;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }
  .domains li:hover { border-color: var(--neon-cyan); box-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.12); }
  .domains .dname { color: var(--text); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .domains .dnum { font-family: var(--crt); color: var(--neon-lime); margin-right: 10px; letter-spacing: 1px; }
  .domains .dweight {
    font-family: var(--crt);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(25, 240, 255, 0.4);
  }

  a.xlink {
    color: var(--neon-lime);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(157, 255, 60, 0.4);
  }
  a.xlink:hover { color: #fff; border-bottom-color: #fff; }
</style>
